definition: headman (of primitive people)/tribal chief/used as translation for foreign leaders, e.g. Indian Rajah or Arab Sheik or Emir

pinyin: A1 la1 bo2 Lian2 he2 Qiu2 zhang3 guo2

definition: Emirate/Sheikdom/used as translation for country under a chief
United Arab Emirates/abbr. for 阿拉伯聯合酋長國|阿拉伯联合酋长国[A1 la1 bo2 Lian2 he2 Qiu2 zhang3 guo2]

sentences.english: The national team of the United Arab Emirates made the lizard.
sentences.chinese: 來自阿拉伯聯合酋長國的隊伍製作了這個蜥蜴。

sentences.english: In governance, the chief must consult with the Council on all important matters.
sentences.chinese: 酋長在管理上的重大問題上必須與議會磋商。

sentences.english: I am Warchief of the Horde, he said proudly.
sentences.chinese: 我是霜狼氏族的酋長，他驕傲地說。

sentences.english: In 1969, Gadhafi overthrew the Eastern tribal King Idris.
sentences.chinese: 1969年，卡扎菲推翻了東部的部落酋長伊德里斯。

sentences.english: Abu Dhabi has nearly all the UAE's oil.
sentences.chinese: 阿聯酋的石油幾乎全部集中在阿布扎比酋長國。

sentences.english: Then, cacique abides by a promise, put them.
sentences.chinese: 於是，酋長遵守諾言，放了他們。

sentences.english: Sveral times the chief tried to get a word in, but to no avail.
sentences.chinese: 酋長几次都想插話，但都被她打斷了。

sentences.english: During the economic collapse, the Arab sheiks are buying extraordinary things.
sentences.chinese: 在經濟崩潰，阿拉伯酋長購買平凡的事情。

sentences.english: The emirate became part of Bauchi state in 1926.
sentences.chinese: 1926年該酋長國成爲包奇州一部分。

sentences.english: She was one of twenty children of Chief Powhatan.
sentences.chinese: 她是酋長Powhatan20個孩子中的一個。

sentences.english: The women glanced toward the doorway, where the sheikh was absorbed in his phone call.
sentences.chinese: 女人們往門口望去，發現酋長還在專注地講電話。

sentences.english: The chief's house contained an audience room forty feet square .
sentences.chinese: 酋長的房裏有一個接見室，四十英尺見方。

sentences.english: The sheik turns to the first man and asks him what he does for a living.
sentences.chinese: 酋長轉向第一個男人問他是靠什麼生計。

sentences.english: This park preserves the birthplace of Chief Sealth.
sentences.chinese: 這個公園是保存司酋長的出生處。

sentences.english: Arab sheikh carves two-miles-long name in sand until it's visible from SPACE.
sentences.chinese: 阿拉伯酋長在沙漠刻兩英里“大”名，太空可見。

sentences.english: The right to elect chieftains and to depose them.
sentences.chinese: 選舉和撤換酋長的權利。
